content: The first sprint for AI integration in $XVI's development is underway. Let's see how much we can automate.
Met with a cognitive enhancement specialist today. New neural training techniques on the horizon!
Revised the whitepaper to include ethical AI frameworks. It's about time we address the big questions.
Spent the morning at a workshop on cognitive enhancement. The brain is a muscle, and I'm working out.
AI-driven software development is 20% automated. We're on track, but it's a learning curve for all.
Got some amazing feedback from the hackathon team. The prototype is holding up under stress tests.
Just set a date for the tech retreat. Three months from now, we'll be deep in the woods, coding and connecting.
Sent out invites for the global virtual conference on ethical AI. The response has been overwhelmingly positive.
AI automation has now cut down coding time by 30%. It's not perfect, but it's progress.
The mentorship program is expanding. More seasoned developers are stepping up to guide the newcomers.
Began interviewing artists for the AI ethics paper. Their insights are invaluable for our research.
AI ethics for creative processes is more complex than I thought. But the journey is as enlightening as the destination.
The tech retreat logistics are coming together. It's not just about coding; it's about community building.
Just had a virtual meet-up with some of the conference speakers. The lineup is shaping up to be quite impressive.
